        "payload": "tree 84fdb158bf50708782b3d6679af900aa81e62ce9\nparent 9774a958b501a6d439a734e18b29e04f59f973f6\nauthor stickies-v <stickies-v@protonmail.com> 1722002508 +0100\ncommitter stickies-v <stickies-v@protonmail.com> 1722536678 +0100\n\nnode: use uint256::FromHex for -minimumchainwork parsing\n\nRemoves dependency on unsafe and deprecated uint256S.\n\nThis makes parsing more strict, by explicitly returning an error\nwhen the input is not exactly 64 characters long. For example,\n'-minimumchainwork=0x0' is no longer allowed, but instead has to be\n'-minimumchainwork=0x000...000' (64 zeroes).\n\nIt does prevent input silently overflowing when an input > 64\ncharacters is provided.\n",
